column9: Good evening
hi benjad
is all well with the interchange?
Yes, I am playing with the numbers a little bit now, trying to network things in, but not fill plants to capacity
be aware that my glass & steel mills are not connected by bulk to the xchange
numbers look pretty good right now.   Gotcha
I'm assuming that at some point, mines will be de-electrified, and will need more capacity down south
whenever jaridan shows up I'm hoping to assume control of the grid. Idk where he's been
Loll.  Good.  Bc i do have one cross country line.. will be good to take it down
but yes, I'll de-electrify the mines
if you want, I can power your southern mine right now...
Do we need to power mines, in the bigger picture?
It depends on how much demand. Atm not really
(but you still want me to power your southern mine for right now?)
Sure, let see how that works out
ok.
cool, now to let it run a while, and see what is needed.  Im ready for some industry growth.  I put some lines out waiting.
cannery @424,222 is avaliable if you want
and if jaridan ever returns and builds up a pax network there's room for another brewery & food fac
cannery is yours.  it's already on your network
I would need steel from the other side of the world, though...
and meat
I'm already set up for both the other steel mills
I'm just waiting on demand
oh, for teh cannery
you might be able to, in the future, run a line from @181, 233
to the brewery, to the glass mill, the supermarket, on to the cannery
hrm... yeah, looking at that now, and hte cannery again
going to deal with teh cannery tomorrow, as it does look viable for me
ok. please take fish from @272,119, if you need more let me supply so no backflow onto my network
yup, and cattle from @66,273    but since meat has a bonus, need to build a big fast line
yes, be prepared to drop serious money on fast lines. The renfe 250 fast electric I use costs over a million credits
and the older deltic almost 800k
you can see I'm still 12 million in the hole!
wow.  yeah.  I also see that Jaridan does need to appear.  His profit is dropping fast
